   "body" : "We currently disable the `shellcheck` rules SC2046 and SC2086 in our `lint-shell.sh` script, however, I think it is important that we enable them and make our scripts conformant and therefore more robust.\r\n\r\nI have encountered many inscrutable build failures where the ultimate culprit was missing quoting, and from personal experience, I think word-splitting is the exception rather than the norm, and it would make our scripts easier to read if instances of word-splitting are pointed out by the shellcheck directives.",
